helpdesk_ticket.description:
To,
The Grievance Officer / Senior Management,
Pharmeasy.
Ref: Order ID: 652916509880352768-FDJ
I am writing this email with extreme distress and anger regarding the gross
negligence and deficiency in service displayed by Pharmeasy regarding my
medical order.
1. Critical Delay in Delivery (Medical Negligence):
I placed an order for critical medicines on 27th November, with a promised
delivery date of 30th November. It has now been 5 days past the due date,
and the delivery is still pending.
These medicines are for my father who suffers from serious Heart and Blood
Pressure issues. Due to your failure to deliver on time, he has missed his
dosage, putting his health in a critical condition. This is not just a
delay in logistics; it is a clear case of Medical Negligence endangering a
patient's life.
2. Staff Misconduct and Harassment:
When I contacted your customer support to resolve this urgency, the
response was appalling:
Incident 1: One agent abruptly disconnected the call while I was explaining
the emergency. I possess the call recording of this incident as evidence.
Incident 2: Another agent spoke to me in an extremely rude, abusive, and
unprofessional manner.
Instead of assisting a customer in a medical emergency, your team resorted
to misconduct, misinformation, and misrepresentation. This constitutes a
severe offense under the Consumer Protection Act, amounting to deficiency
of service and unfair trade practices.
MY DEMANDS:
I demand the following immediately:
Immediate Delivery: The medicines must be delivered within the next 12-24
hours.
Action Taken Report: I need a written reply detailing the disciplinary
action taken against the two agents involved in the misconduct.
Compensation: I demand compensation for the mental harassment, agony, and
the health risk caused to my father due to this delay.
LEGAL WARNING:
Please treat this email as a formal notice. If I do not receive a
satisfactory response and the delivery immediately, I will be compelled to:
File a formal complaint in the Consumer Court for deficiency of service and
endangering life.
Lodge a complaint regarding the staff's abusive behavior.
Escalate this matter on social media and relevant health regulatory bodies.
I expect a reply from a senior executive immediately.
Regards,
Harivansh Dagar
(Advocate)

--

helpdesk_ticket.subject: ✨ Body Language Power Skills: Elevate Your Influence & Communication
helpdesk_ticket.description_html:
Decode the Messages/p>
 

Understand Emotions, Signals & Intentions
Body language forms the invisible layer of communication that reveals emotions, intentions and unspoken truths long before words are spoken. This immersive masterclass equips you with the ability to read subtle cues—facial expressions, eye contact, posture, gestures and micro-signals—so you can understand what people are truly thinking and feeling. Through engaging activities and real-world scenarios, you’ll learn to distinguish between positive signals such as open posture and genuine smiles, and negative cues like fidgeting or crossed arms that indicate discomfort or resistance. As you strengthen your own nonverbal presence and interpret others with greater accuracy, you will communicate more clearly, connect more deeply and navigate interpersonal interactions with newfound confidence and insight
For enquiries, please contact Ms Calista at Whatsapp: 8040 9568 │ Call: 6720 3333┃ Email: training.aventis@gmail.com
 

Learning Outcomes

By the end of the workshop, you will be equipped with following skills:
  • Enhance Emotional Awareness: Develop a heightened awareness of the emotions and feelings of those around you, enabling more empathetic and effective interactions.
  • Detect Negative Energy: Identify and sense the overall atmosphere in a room, allowing you to recognize and address negative vibes before they escalate.
  • Sharpen Intuitive Skills: Improve your ability to read people accurately, honing a skill often referred to as intuition, which enhances your interpersonal effectiveness.
  • Mitigate Deception: Reduce costly mistakes caused by misinterpreting individuals; gain the confidence to discern truth from deception, ensuring you are not easily misled.
  • Elevate Personal Presence: Enhance your own body language and executive presence, allowing you to communicate with greater authority and authenticity while effectively reading unspoken cues—whether they are things that others don’t say, can’t say, unconsciously reveal, or intentionally conceal.

Course Details
 
Course Title: The Secrets of Interpreting Body Language Masterclass
Course Fees: SGD 680.00 (excluding GST)
Eligible NTUC members can claim up to 50% off total course fees via UTAP Funding after course completion!
 
For enquiries, please contact Ms Calista at Whatsapp: 8040 9568 │ Call: 6720 3333 ┃ Email: training.aventis@gmail.com
 
 

Classroom Session

HRP Code: AV239

Date: 05 Jan 2026 (Mon)
Time: 9.00 am to 5.00 pm
Venue: Holiday Inn Orchard City Centre/ Concorde Hotel
Don't Miss Out on our December Special: 10% OFF when you register with a buddy — plus 50% UTAP funding!
🍽️ Buffet lunch and refreshments included for all participants
Register for Classroom Session
 
 

Course Outline
Module 1: Understanding Emotions Through Body Language
  • Explore how emotions are reflected in non-verbal cues such as facial expressions, posture, and gestures.
  • Identify the six basic emotional types and their corresponding body language signals.
Module 2: Techniques for Observing and Analyzing Body Language
  • Learn the baseline technique to understand normal behavior patterns.
  • Spot deviations that may indicate underlying emotions or concealed truths.
  • Practice identifying red flags and "tells" through analysis of still photos and videos.
Module 3: Positive and Negative Gestures in Communication
  • Differentiate between positive and negative gestures and their impact on communication.
  • Understand how to interpret common cues to build rapport or address concerns.
  • Participate in exercises to internalize gesture recognition skills.
Module 4: Enhancing and Projecting Your Body Language
  • Gain awareness of your own body language and how it influences perceptions.
  • Learn techniques to project a confident self-image in professional and personal interactions.
  • Engage in classroom activities and real-life case studies to reinforce learning
